race.comment: FRENZY LUNE (10) has a moderate winning strike-rate but did a good job when returning from a break for a new stable last time at Moe, finishing second and only a long neck from the winner at the end of 1000m. Likely improver with strong prospects. ALPINOVA (1) made progress last time out, finishing 2.75 lengths from the winner in second at the end of 1209m at Yarra Valley. Suitably placed so anticipating another big run. TRINITY'S D'ORO (3) doesn't boast the best winning strike rate but ran a strong race last time out, finishing third and beaten only a neck over 1600m at Moe. Can play a big role. SINISTER SAUCE (6) has been jumping out adequately at Flemington and this is easier than a lot of the races she contested  last preparation, so gets a big chance to return with a bang.
